<br>
Congrats to Panamah, Jakle and Trew for organizing such an event - I applaud your intent, but you have to admit you had a large number of people who attended who were unruly, disruptive and extremely selfish. Why would you want to help get such people flagged for higher planes? So they can pollute another high level zone with /ooc sup! and /ooc hey bro! LFG!<br>
<br>
The way I see it, lower tier zones *should* end up being catchall zones. You should IMO have to (a) work your ass off in a guild or (b) work your ass off unguilded to retain a good reputation, to gain access to the upper planes.<br>
<br>
The endgame in EQ isnt a free for all - it is highly group oriented. Just because you buy the expansion doesnt mean that you automatically get access to all zones. I have been playing since before release and I still havent seen VT, ST, or VP and I sure as hell dont feel like the upper tiers of PoP are an entitlement.<br>
<br>
Not bashing. Not trying to be a snob. Not questioning motives.<br>
<br>
Just questioning the result.<br>
<br>
Trewayn, like him or not - and I am not a big fan after his &quot;Mojoo is a c**nt&quot; rant - worked damn hard (along with the other organizers), what did he get? - a flag and a bunch of unnecessary abuse. Why you would want freeloading scum like that Darenenski character to be flagged for CoD is just beyond me...<br>
