<br>
So many of my friends have quit EQ, moved to other servers, left for bigger guilds and the soul reason was PoP.   They all paid exactly the same price you did to purchase PoP, they all pay the same monthly price to be able to do things.  The one thing they haven't done is left their small group of friends behind, generally, to join a big guild and get flags.<br>
<br>
Most guilds have been growing like mad since PoP came out since the people that passed PoJ trials found out how badly stuck they are in 1 or 2 zones night after night.  Even with that a lot of the not-so-uber guilds still don't quite have enough people or levels to be able to pass these flagging events by themselves.  No offense, but I don't think most people who are in large guilds getting lots of flags really have much empathy for others who are getting left behind.<br>
<br>
Even some of your own guildmates are getting flagged at these events.  Do you really want to be repeating these over and over endlessly or would it benefit The Kindred and other large, capable guilds, to send along their unflagged rather than having to do this ad nauseum?<br>
<br>
These people on our raids are some of the nicest, kindest, fun people on the server.  And you're saying they don't have the right to play in more than a couple of zones for xp simply because of their guild affliation?  Lets think this through a minute.  The small, family type guilds tend to be a little less competitive over spawns, very concerned about getting along with other people and keeping their reputations pristine.  Larger guilds tend to compete harder for spawns.  If we force everyone into large guilds, everyone is going to have to compete that much harder for everything.  I think the culture and value of small guilds to the server is an important one to preserve and I think the open raids and helping each other to get flagged is the way to keep them viable.<br>
<br>
Conversely there's some real a**holes in guilds that are getting tons of flags.  I'm sure you can't deny this.<br>
<br>
